'''Bec du Gave''' is the point at which the [[Gaves réunis]] stream meets the [[Adour]] River in southwestern France.<ref name='hugh'>{{cite book | last = McKnight | first = Hugh | authorlink = | coauthors = | title = Cruising French Waterways, 4th Edition | publisher = Sheridan House| year = 2005 | pages = | isbn =978-0-8124-0152-3 }}</ref>   The ''Chateau du Bec du Gave''[https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=fr&u=http://www.port-de-lanne.fr/chateau.html&ei=6rirS9LCHsX7lwfx8-m0Dg&sa=X&oi=translate&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CBAQ7gEwAg&prev=/search%3Fq%3DCh%25C3%25A2teau%2Bdu%2BBec%2Bdu%2BGave%26hl%3Den] is located nearby.  Nearest village is [[Port-de-Lanne]].

