{{Orphan|date=May 2011}}

The '''Filchner Trough''' ({{coord|77|S|36|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea trough extending north from its associated feature, the [[Filchner Ice Shelf]]. The name, proposed by Dr. [[Heinrich Hinze]] of the [[Alfred Wegener Institute for Polar and Marine Research]], [[Bremerhaven, Germany]], was approved by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in June 1997.<ref name=gnis/>

