This is a '''list of legislatures by size'''. Non-sovereign entities are marked in ''italics''.

==Examples==
<gallery>
File:13th PRC National People's Congress Diagram.svg|The indirectly elected [[National People's Congress]] of China is the largest legislature in the world, by number of members.
File:House of Lords 2017.svg|The [[Parliament of the United Kingdom]] is the largest bicameral legislature, with 1,443 members. The unelected [[House of Lords]] is the largest [[upper house]], with 793 members.
File:Bundestag (current composition).svg|The [[Bundestag]], which functions as Germany's [[lower house]], is the second largest unicameral directly elected national legislature in the world.
File:Pontifical Commission.svg|The [[Pontifical Commission for Vatican City State]] is the smallest legislature by a sovereign state, with just 7 members all appointed by the Pope.
File:Palau Senate.svg|The [[Palau National Congress]], is the smallest bicameral legislature, with 25 members, its [[Senate of Palau|Senate]], is the smallest upper house, with 9 elected members.
File:Grenada House of Representatives seats.svg|The [[Parliament of Grenada]]'s lower house is the smallest directly elected assembly in the world, with 15 elected members.
</gallery>

