'''Location inference''' is the method of identifying the location profiles of users on [[social media]] platforms such as [[Twitter]]<ref>{{Cite journal|title = A survey of location inference techniques on Twitter|url = http://jis.sagepub.com/content/41/6/855|journal = Journal of Information Science|date = 2015-12-01|issn = 0165-5515|pages = 855–864|volume = 41|issue = 6|doi = 10.1177/0165551515602847|first = O.|last = Ajao|first2 = J.|last2 = Hong|first3 = W.|last3 = Liu|arxiv = 1701.03639}}</ref> and [[Facebook]] from their message content, friends' network and social interaction even when they did not explicitly disclose such on their account profiles or [[Geotagging|geotag]] their messages.

Applications of location inference includes [[Emergency management|disaster management]] such as locating victims of earthquakes, consumer profiling for [[targeted advertising]], tailored news content and for law enforcement such as detection of [[cyberbullying]] culprits.

