{{About|a mountain pass|the battle in the Korean War|Battle of Triangle Hill|the Chinese war film|Battle on Shangganling Mountain}} {{Unreferenced|date=June 2009}} {{Infobox Korean name | hangul = 상감령 | hanja = {{linktext|上|甘|嶺}} | rr = Sanggamryeong | mr = Sanggamryŏng | context = north | img = Triangle Hill.gif | caption = Map of the Triangle Hill Complex, Sanggamryŏng is located at the Y junction behind Jane Russell Hill }} {{Infobox Korean name | title = Triangle Hill | hangul = 삼각고지 | hanja = {{linktext|三|角|高|地}} | rr = Samgakgoji | mr = Samgakkoji }}
'''Sanggamryŏng''', also known as '''Shangganling''' ({{Zh|s=上甘岭|p=Shànggānlǐng}}) in Chinese, '''Triangle Hill''' ({{lang-ko|3각고지}}) in South Korea, and '''Jane & Russell Hill''' in United States is a [[mountain pass]] in central [[North Korea]].
The mountain pass is part of the '''Triangle Hill Complex''' that is roughly 4&nbsp;km north by northeast of [[Kimhwa]]. Situated in the valley between the Jane Russell Hill and the Sniper Ridge, the hamlet became famous in China due to the [[Battle of Shangganling]], a large-scale battle in the [[Korean War]]. By the time the fighting broke out, the hamlet had already been leveled by bombings with most of its residents displaced, thus it played no role in the battle itself.
