{{Infobox settlement <!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage--> <!-- Basic info ----------------> | official_name = Santa Coloma | native_name = Santa Coloma d'Andorra | other_name = Santa Coloma of Andorra | settlement_type = <!--For Town or Village (Leave blank for the default City)--> <!-- images and maps -----------> | image_skyline = Santa_Coloma_Andorra.jpg | image_caption = Santa Coloma and the [[Gran Valira]] river (right) as seen from a nearby mountain | image_flag = | image_seal = | image_shield = | nickname = | motto = | image_map = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = Andorra | pushpin_image = Andorra relief location map.jpg | pushpin_label_position = left | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Andorra | coordinates = {{coord|42|29|38.03|N|1|29|51.66|E|region:AD|display=inline,title}} <!-- Location ------------------> | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{Flag|Andorra}} | subdivision_type1 = Parish | subdivision_name1 = [[Andorra la Vella]] | subdivision_type2 = | subdivision_name2 = | established_title = <!-- Settled --> | established_date = | government_type = <!-- Politics -----------------> | government_footnotes = | leader_title = | leader_name = <!-- Area ---------------------> | unit_pref = Metric <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired--> | area_footnotes = | area_total_km2 = <!-- ALL fields dealing with a measurements are subject to automatic unit conversion--> | area_land_km2 = <!--See table @ Template:Infobox Settlement for details on automatic unit conversion--> | area_water_km2 = | area_water_percent = | elevation_footnotes = <!--for references: use<ref> </ref> tags--> | elevation_m = 1134 <!-- Population -----------------------> | population_footnotes = | population_total = 3040 | population_as_of = 2012 | population_density_km2 = auto | population_note = <!-- General information ---------------> | timezone = GMT +1 | utc_offset = | timezone_DST = | utc_offset_DST = <!-- Area/postal codes & others --------> | postal_code_type = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... --> | postal_code = | area_code = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Santa Coloma d'Andorra''' ('''Santa Coloma of Andorra''', {{IPA-ca|ˈsantə kuˈlomə ðənˈdorə}}) or briefly '''Santa Coloma''' is an [[Andorra]]n town in the parish of [[Andorra la Vella]], located near the [[Gran Valira]] river and 2&nbsp;km away from the capital, Andorra la Vella.<ref name="andorralavella">{{cite web| url=https://turisme.andorralavella.ad/en/node/193/santa-coloma | title=Santa Coloma | website=turisme.andorralavella.ad | publisher=Andorra la Vella | location=Andorra | accessdate=11 October 2017 }}</ref>
==Geography== To its west are the mountain villages of [[Aixàs]], [[Bixessarri]], and [[Canòlic]] in Andorra, and [[Os de Civís]] in [[Spain]].{{citation needed|date=July 2012}}
==Notable buildings== It houses a [[Església de Santa Coloma d'Andorra|historic church]] that was nominated as a [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage]] site on 22&nbsp;February 1999 in the Cultural category.<ref>[http://whc.unesco.org/en/tentativelists/1268/ Ensemble historique de Santa Coloma], [[UNESCO]] World Heritage Centre.</ref>
