'''Silver sand''' is a fine white [[sand]] used in [[gardening]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/silver-sand|title=silver sand - definition of silver sand in English from the Oxford dictionary|work=oxforddictionaries.com}}</ref> It consists largely of [[quartz]] particles that are not coated with [[iron oxide]]s. [[Iron]] oxides colour sand from [[yellow]]s to rich [[brown]]s. Silver sand is also used as a constituent of [[mortar (masonry)|mortar]] for laying light coloured [[paver (flooring)|pavers]].

